For An Act To Be Entitled
8
9 AN ACT CONCERNING THE MEMBERSHIP OF THE ARKANSAS
10 TEACHER RETIREMENT SYSTEM; TO ESTABLISH THE CREATING
11 AN INVESTMENT OPPORTUNITY FOR EARLY CHILDHOOD WORKERS
12 ACT OF 2025; AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES.
13
14
Subtitle
15
16 TO ESTABLISH THE CREATING AN INVESTMENT
17 OPPORTUNITY FOR EARLY CHILDHOOD WORKERS
18 ACT OF 2025.
19
20 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
21
22 SECTION 1. DO NOT CODIFY. Legislative intent.
23 It is the intent of the General Assembly to:
24 (1) Provide a voluntary mechanism for early childhood workers to
25 participate in the Arkansas Teacher Retirement System; and
26 (2) Require no expenditure of state funds for matching of any
27 contributions for early childhood workers who are not otherwise eligible for
28 participation in the Arkansas Teacher Retirement System.
29
30 SECTION 2. Arkansas Code § 24-7-202(21), concerning the definition of
31 "employment with a school" as it applies to the Arkansas Teacher Retirement
32 System, is amended to add an additional subdivision to read as follows:
33 (H) Employment of an early childhood worker as defined by
34 § 24-7-212(b), with a licensed childcare facility that provides teaching,
35 early childcare education, or supervision for a child enrolled in a licensed
36 childcare facility under the Childcare Licensing Act, § 20-78-201 et seq.;"
