03-12-2025 10:10:15 LJH108

As Engrossed: S3/12/25 SB148
1
2 SECTION 3. Arkansas Code Title 24, Chapter 7, Subchapter 2, is amended
3 to add an additional section to read as follows:
4 24-7-212. Creating an Investment Opportunity for Early Childhood
5 Workers Act of 2025 — Definition.
6 (a) This section shall be known and may be cited as the "Creating an
7 Investment Opportunity for Early Childhood Workers Act of 2025."
8 (b) As used in this section, "early childhood worker" means a person
9 who is:
10 (1) Providing teaching, early childcare education, or
11 supervision for a child enrolled in a licensed childcare facility under the
12 Childcare Facility Licensing Act, § 20-78-201 et seq.;
13 (2) Employed by a childcare provider that is licensed and
14 regulated by the Department of Education as an appropriate early childhood
15 program as defined under § 6-45-103; and
16 (3) Employed by a childcare provider that receives state or
17 federal child care funding from the Department of Education under § 6-87-101.
18 (c)(1) A single nonprofit fiscal agent that is approved by the Board
19 of Trustees of the Arkansas Teacher Retirement System may act as a pass-
20 through fiscal agent to facilitate the voluntary participation of an early
21 childhood worker in the Arkansas Teacher Retirement System.
22 (2) The board shall authorize participation consistent with §
23 24-7-202(21)(F)(i) and § 24-7-202(21)(F)(ii).
24 (3) Membership in the system is not mandatory for an employee of
25 a facility regardless of whether the board authorizes participation under
26 subdivision (c)(2) of this section.
27 (d) An early childhood worker shall not be entitled to:
28 (1) Contribution from state funds; or
29 (2) Matching from the state or the system.
30 (e) The board shall promulgate rules for the implementation of this
31 section.
32
